1
00:00:04,604 --> 00:00:06,906
As you all know,

2
00:00:06,973 --> 00:00:08,808
when it comes to criminal cases,

3
00:00:08,875 --> 00:00:13,380
Japan is often considered to be
behind other countries.

4
00:00:13,446 --> 00:00:16,449
For instance, in many countries,

5
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:19,486
the suspect has the right

6
00:00:19,552 --> 00:00:23,523
to have an attorney present
during questioning.

7
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:25,558
This is not the case in Japan.

8
00:00:25,625 --> 00:00:28,762
If the suspect denies the crime,
their detention is extended.

9
00:00:28,828 --> 00:00:32,265
If they admit to the crime,
they are granted bail.

10
00:00:32,332 --> 00:00:36,903
Some refer to this system
as "hostage justice," and criticize it.

11
00:00:37,404 --> 00:00:40,940
It sounds as if
the suspect is held hostage

12
00:00:41,007 --> 00:00:44,878
and coerced into confessing.

13
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:48,181
Absurd!

14
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,586
Also, it is most regrettable

15
00:00:53,653 --> 00:00:56,222
that due to the unlawful actions
of one prosecutor,

16
00:00:56,289 --> 00:00:59,559
trust in the prosecution
has been significantly shaken.

17
00:01:00,493 --> 00:01:01,995
This is truly disappointing.

18
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:04,531
My sincere apologies.

19
00:01:05,665 --> 00:01:08,101
My sincere apologies.

20
00:01:08,168 --> 00:01:11,571
Now, what will we do?

21
00:01:12,305 --> 00:01:16,443
Here today, I want to strongly declare

22
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:23,016
that we should not be cowed
and that we should remain confident!

23
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:25,885
We, the prosecution, obey the law,

24
00:01:25,952 --> 00:01:29,322
are faithful to our duties,
and do what must be done.

25
00:01:29,389 --> 00:01:30,390
In the first place,

26
00:01:31,224 --> 00:01:36,262
<i>the people want
guilty individuals to be punished.</i>

27
00:01:36,329 --> 00:01:40,834
<i>We have taken their will seriously</i>

28
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,269
<i>and have been seeking the truth.</i>

29
00:01:43,336 --> 00:01:47,140
<i>That is precisely how we've maintained</i>

30
00:01:47,207 --> 00:01:53,046
a conviction rate of 99.9%,
a rarity even globally!

31
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:57,016
Now is the time to restore
the authority of the prosecution…

32
00:01:58,885 --> 00:02:01,421
and show the world

33
00:02:02,088 --> 00:02:06,993
that we, the prosecution,
represent justice!

34
00:02:23,009 --> 00:02:26,146
I'm truly sorry!

35
00:02:26,679 --> 00:02:28,615
But I won't let it end here.

36
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:31,584
We're working on finding a way

37
00:02:32,252 --> 00:02:33,586
to get a retrial as soon as--

38
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:34,787
Thank you.

39
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:40,927
I don't blame my situation on you.

40
00:02:42,462 --> 00:02:44,397
My dabbling in embezzlement

41
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:47,267
and my false confession…

42
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,470
They were all due to my own weakness.

43
00:02:52,672 --> 00:02:55,608
There's no reason for you to apologize.

44
00:02:56,276 --> 00:03:02,148
You're the one who sacrificed
so much of your life for me and Saya.

45
00:03:05,251 --> 00:03:06,452
It must've felt so long.

46
00:03:08,154 --> 00:03:09,756
Thanks to you…

47
00:03:12,058 --> 00:03:13,593
I was able to see Saya again.

48
00:03:14,761 --> 00:03:18,164
Even yesterday, she showed me a picture.

49
00:03:19,966 --> 00:03:22,635
Here are Mill and Mame.

50
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:24,170
Don't they look just like Cocoa?

51
00:03:24,737 --> 00:03:27,173
I can't wait to show them to you.

52
00:03:35,415 --> 00:03:36,482
My hands…

53
00:03:38,418 --> 00:03:39,752
are warm.

54
00:03:43,456 --> 00:03:44,390
I'm…

55
00:03:45,792 --> 00:03:46,893
alive right now.

56
00:03:48,995 --> 00:03:50,597
I was able to feel that again.

57
00:03:55,501 --> 00:03:57,170
And that’s truly enough for me.

58
00:03:57,704 --> 00:03:58,705
Mr. Shimizu!

59
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,140
You have every right…

60
00:04:02,141 --> 00:04:04,577
to experience more happiness!

61
00:04:07,046 --> 00:04:10,083
I promised to secure an acquittal for you.

62
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:12,552
Please give me

63
00:04:12,619 --> 00:04:14,120
just a little more…

64
00:04:18,024 --> 00:04:19,459
a little more time.

65
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:27,700
ITOI FAMILY MURDERS CASE
INVESTIGATIVE REPORT

66
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:32,905
Mr. Akizumi isn't coming out today either.

67
00:04:32,972 --> 00:04:34,774
It seems he isn't even going home.

68
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:38,177
He's reviewing the case files
he has already reviewed many times.

69
00:04:38,244 --> 00:04:40,880
By the way, did you meet
the reporter acquainted with Ms. Sawahara?

70
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,716
I learned a lot about
the circumstances from 12 years ago,

71
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:45,985
but nothing decisive
that would lead to a retrial.

72
00:04:46,052 --> 00:04:47,553
I shouldn't be surprised.

73
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:49,989
Finding new evidence isn't so easy.

74
00:04:50,056 --> 00:04:53,159
After all, it took five years
to find that alibi footage.

75
00:04:53,226 --> 00:04:54,494
I'm back.

76
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,395
Hey.

77
00:04:55,461 --> 00:04:56,729
How did it go with your dad?

78
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:58,331
He refused to see me.

79
00:04:58,398 --> 00:04:59,932
But I'll keep going

80
00:04:59,999 --> 00:05:02,201
until he agrees
to testify about the footage.

81
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:03,336
Please do.

82
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:05,538
We don't have
any other options at the moment.

83
00:05:09,609 --> 00:05:11,210
What's the matter, youngster?

84
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:13,613
How about we sort things out once?

85
00:05:20,687 --> 00:05:23,323
<i>On March 5th, 2012,
at Mr. Makoto Itoi's home</i>

86
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:26,926
<i>in Hanamigawa Ward,
Chiba City, Chiba Prefecture,</i>

87
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:29,796
<i>his whole family was found dead.</i>

88
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,899
<i>The night before,
the family had consulted a doctor,</i>

89
00:05:32,965 --> 00:05:36,035
<i>citing symptoms
such as vomiting and diarrhea.</i>

90
00:05:36,636 --> 00:05:38,571
<i>But they passed away before dawn.</i>

91
00:05:39,272 --> 00:05:40,740
<i>After the on-site investigation,</i>

92
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:43,142
<i>a high concentration
of thallium was detected,</i>

93
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:45,211
<i>leading to the conclusion of poisoning.</i>

94
00:05:45,978 --> 00:05:47,947
<i>According to neighbors,</i>

95
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:50,416
<i>around 7:30 p.m. on the night
before their deaths,</i>

96
00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:53,686
<i>the Itoi family hosted
a dinner party with a guest.</i>

97
00:05:54,721 --> 00:05:55,655
<i>The police investigated</i>

98
00:05:55,722 --> 00:05:59,292
<i>under the assumption
that this guest brought in the poison.</i>

99
00:06:00,593 --> 00:06:07,333
<i>No hair, sebum, skin, or any other trace
of the culprit was found at the scene.</i>

100
00:06:08,301 --> 00:06:10,837
<i>Everyone related to Mr. Itoi
was thoroughly investigated,</i>

101
00:06:10,903 --> 00:06:16,342
<i>resulting in the arrest of Mr. Shimizu,
who was close to the family.</i>

102
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:18,010
However, on the night in question,

103
00:06:18,077 --> 00:06:21,547
Mr. Shimizu was actually searching
for Saya's stuffed animal in Hishimi Park.

104
00:06:21,614 --> 00:06:23,116
According to Ms. Momose's file,

105
00:06:23,182 --> 00:06:27,320
<i>Mr. Shimizu was seen on covert footage
captured by Mr. Hiyama at 7:41 p.m.</i>

106
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:34,994
On the other hand, the suspected culprit
visited the Itoi home around 7:30 p.m.

107
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:35,995
Given the distance,

108
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:39,365
it was impossible for Mr. Shimizu
to be at Mr. Itoi's home at that time.

109
00:06:39,932 --> 00:06:43,836
However, no one was aware of the existence
of the footage at that point.

110
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:47,740
And only Saya knew
that Mr. Shimizu had gone to a park.

111
00:06:47,807 --> 00:06:48,875
The police believed

112
00:06:48,941 --> 00:06:52,111
Mr. Shimizu had coached
his 5-year-old daughter to say things.

113
00:06:52,178 --> 00:06:54,814
Additionally, evidence
of his embezzlement of company funds

114
00:06:54,881 --> 00:06:57,216
and his conflicts
with Mr. Itoi were uncovered,

115
00:06:57,283 --> 00:06:59,218
further intensifying
suspicion against him.

116
00:06:59,852 --> 00:07:03,556
I suggest you all go through this as well.

117
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:08,594
ITOI FAMILY MURDERS CASE

118
00:07:08,661 --> 00:07:11,798
I wonder what Ms. Momose was like.

119
00:07:11,864 --> 00:07:13,399
She was quite accomplished.

120
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,001
What?

121
00:07:15,067 --> 00:07:16,669
Mr. Aoyama, you knew her too?

122
00:07:16,736 --> 00:07:18,538
She was my junior at university.

123
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:21,340
I also aspired to become an attorney
back then, you know.

124
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,510
Is that when you got acquainted
with Mr. Akizumi, then?

125
00:07:24,577 --> 00:07:25,545
Yes.

126
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:28,181
I tried the bar exam
four times, but failed.

127
00:07:28,247 --> 00:07:32,051
Despite how he may seem,
he can get extremely nervous.

128
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:36,055
When my wife became pregnant,
I gave up and took a job as a salesperson.

129
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:38,758
But I reconnected
with Mr. Akizumi five years ago.

130
00:07:40,593 --> 00:07:44,464
That's when I learned
about Ms. Momose's passing.

131
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:47,867
When I see your notebooks, Mr. Akamine,

132
00:07:47,934 --> 00:07:49,702
they remind me of Ms. Momose.

133
00:07:49,769 --> 00:07:52,271
She used to take notes just like you.

134
00:08:11,224 --> 00:08:13,759
Quite a while ago,

135
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:18,397
I handed things I thought might be related
to the incident over to Mr. Akizumi.

136
00:08:18,464 --> 00:08:20,900
But as I was organizing,
I found some more.

137
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:23,002
Thank you very much.

138
00:08:24,537 --> 00:08:25,538
Come in.

139
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:31,210
She was investigating Mr. Shimizu's case…

140
00:08:32,578 --> 00:08:34,680
the entire time she was in the hospital.

141
00:08:35,882 --> 00:08:40,486
She questioned the doctors about poisons
and gave them a hard time.

142
00:08:42,088 --> 00:08:42,922
Go ahead.

143
00:09:00,973 --> 00:09:04,343
This is the diary Reiko kept
until she passed away.

144
00:09:04,911 --> 00:09:06,012
I couldn't…

145
00:09:06,078 --> 00:09:10,716
I'm already grateful that Mr. Akizumi
is carrying on Reiko's wish.

146
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:16,989
And now, with another ally like you…

147
00:09:18,157 --> 00:09:19,692
she must be pleased.

148
00:09:24,764 --> 00:09:26,365
Since she was insistent…

149
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,603
I'm sure Mr. Shimizu is innocent.

150
00:09:31,370 --> 00:09:33,372
Please help save Mr. Shimizu.

151
00:09:40,446 --> 00:09:41,514
<i>I'm back.</i>

152
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:42,715
Welcome back.

153
00:09:43,649 --> 00:09:44,884
Are those Ms. Momose's?

154
00:09:47,219 --> 00:09:49,288
Look at all these labels!

155
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:51,357
I thought her notes might contain clues.

156
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:53,392
Was her mother well?

157
00:09:53,459 --> 00:09:54,594
Yes.

158
00:09:55,795 --> 00:09:56,629
Here.

159
00:09:57,997 --> 00:09:59,532
It's Ms. Momose's diary.

160
00:10:18,050 --> 00:10:19,418
<i>April 1st.</i>

161
00:10:19,986 --> 00:10:22,355
<i>I've been assigned
to work under the Mr. Datehara!</i>

162
00:10:23,389 --> 00:10:27,193
<i>He's the prosecutor
everyone in prosecution looks up to.</i>

163
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:28,628
<i>I'll do my best.</i>

164
00:10:30,429 --> 00:10:31,764
<i>June 10th.</i>

165
00:10:31,831 --> 00:10:35,334
<i>I heard something troubling
about Mr. Datehara.</i>

166
00:10:37,203 --> 00:10:40,172
<i>In the Itoi family murders case in Chiba,</i>

167
00:10:40,239 --> 00:10:43,709
<i>he supposedly suppressed evidence
that could have proven Shimizu's alibi.</i>

168
00:10:43,776 --> 00:10:46,112
Here's the report
on the theft case in Shinjuku.

169
00:10:46,178 --> 00:10:47,613
<i>Because of that incident…</i>

170
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:48,514
Good work.

171
00:10:48,581 --> 00:10:51,651
<i>Mr. Datehara was promoted
to Deputy Chief Prosecutor.</i>

172
00:10:53,252 --> 00:10:54,120
Is something wrong?

173
00:10:54,787 --> 00:10:55,955
Nothing.

174
00:10:56,022 --> 00:10:57,189
Excuse me.

175
00:10:57,256 --> 00:10:59,258
<i>It's difficult to believe.</i>

176
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:00,493
<i>But…</i>

177
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:02,495
<i>if true, it's terrible.</i>

178
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:06,932
<i>June 21st.</i>

179
00:11:06,999 --> 00:11:09,135
<i>I discussed this with a colleague.</i>

180
00:11:09,869 --> 00:11:13,639
<i>I heard that Akizumi was brought in
to assist back then.</i>

181
00:11:13,706 --> 00:11:16,275
After some digging,
things really are strange.

182
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:20,246
Shimizu readily confessed
to the embezzlement charges,

183
00:11:20,312 --> 00:11:22,648
but he consistently denied the murders.

184
00:11:23,549 --> 00:11:25,618
Even his detention period…

185
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:28,020
totaled 65 days.

186
00:11:28,087 --> 00:11:31,090
It was extended
for fabricated reasons, wasn't it?

187
00:11:31,624 --> 00:11:34,627
I'm starting to think he might have been
coerced into confessing.

188
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:37,496
Akizumi, do you know anything--

189
00:11:37,563 --> 00:11:38,397
Any evidence?

190
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:42,601
Evidence that Mr. Datehara covered it up.

191
00:11:43,102 --> 00:11:43,936
I don't--

192
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:46,472
If it's just rumors,
it's not worth verifying.

193
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:48,974
As a prosecutor,
you should have better things to do.

194
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:51,644
We already have
enough criminals to deal with.

195
00:11:54,146 --> 00:11:55,781
<i>I later learned</i>

196
00:11:55,848 --> 00:11:59,785
<i>that it was Akizumi
who coerced Mr. Shimizu into confessing.</i>

197
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:03,956
<i>It was a mistake to seek his advice.</i>

198
00:12:07,026 --> 00:12:08,494
<i>September 6th.</i>

199
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:10,162
<i>I met Detective Fukazawa.</i>

200
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:14,900
<i>It seems that rumors about Mr. Datehara
were started because of what he let slip.</i>

201
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:17,203
A woman came to us
because she was harassed

202
00:12:17,269 --> 00:12:19,939
by someone who sent her
a secretly taken video.

203
00:12:20,706 --> 00:12:22,708
When she showed it to me…

204
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:26,011
-You saw Mr. Shimizu in it.
-Yes.

205
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:30,015
<i>He admitted that the video really existed.</i>

206
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:33,786
So, I reported it to Mr. Kurata, who was
the chief of investigations on this case.

207
00:12:33,853 --> 00:12:35,387
What did Mr. Kurata say?

208
00:12:35,454 --> 00:12:38,791
He said he wanted to examine it carefully
and asked me to hand it over.

209
00:12:38,858 --> 00:12:40,025
So, I did.

210
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:45,297
Later, I was informed that the man
in the video wasn't Shimizu.

211
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:47,066
But looking back…

212
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:49,769
Could you testify to this?

213
00:12:49,835 --> 00:12:51,937
No, of course not.

214
00:12:52,004 --> 00:12:54,406
And keep what I've just told you
to yourself as well.

215
00:12:54,473 --> 00:12:55,574
If you'll excuse me.

216
00:12:55,641 --> 00:12:56,742
Mr. Fukazawa!

217
00:12:58,744 --> 00:13:01,147
<i>Mr. Shimizu was definitely
wrongly accused.</i>

218
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:03,315
<i>This is a big step forward.</i>

219
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:08,220
-Could you please ask him again?
<i>-October 26th.</i>

220
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:10,990
<i>Mr. Shimizu still refuses to meet with me.</i>

221
00:13:11,991 --> 00:13:14,760
<i>I hope he reads my letter.</i>

222
00:13:15,327 --> 00:13:16,962
<i>March 12th.</i>

223
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:21,033
<i>I learned that Mr. Shimizu's daughter
has been frequenting this dog shelter.</i>

224
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,102
You're Saya, right?

225
00:13:23,169 --> 00:13:24,870
<i>Saya Makino.</i>

226
00:13:26,038 --> 00:13:28,641
<i>I hope to gradually grow closer to her.</i>

227
00:13:29,508 --> 00:13:31,010
<i>May 8th.</i>

228
00:13:31,076 --> 00:13:35,047
<i>Cocoa, Saya's dog,
finally warmed up to me!</i>

229
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:40,786
<i>Saya is starting to smile more around me.</i>

230
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,022
Get ready, everyone!

231
00:13:43,088 --> 00:13:44,290
Ms. Momose, hurry!

232
00:13:44,356 --> 00:13:45,591
Right.

233
00:13:51,197 --> 00:13:52,364
Oh, it worked.

234
00:13:53,766 --> 00:13:55,334
<i>October 2nd.</i>

235
00:13:55,401 --> 00:13:57,803
<i>I was transferred
to the Utsunomiya office.</i>

236
00:13:58,404 --> 00:14:01,407
<i>It's uncommon for transfers
to occur at this time of year.</i>

237
00:14:02,608 --> 00:14:06,779
<i>Perhaps this is evidence
that I'm getting closer to the truth.</i>

238
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,683
<i>March 27th.</i>

239
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:12,985
<i>I'm swamped with work.</i>

240
00:14:13,652 --> 00:14:17,156
<i>I wish I could go to Chiba
on the weekend at least</i>

241
00:14:17,223 --> 00:14:19,124
<i>to continue investigating the case.</i>

242
00:14:23,729 --> 00:14:25,497
<i>I don't feel very well.</i>

243
00:14:26,498 --> 00:14:28,033
<i>It might be fatigue.</i>

244
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:32,338
<i>April 7th.</i>

245
00:14:32,404 --> 00:14:33,873
<i>I was diagnosed with an illness.</i>

246
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:36,308
<i>I feel helpless.</i>

247
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:40,112
<i>I don't have time to be hospitalized.</i>

248
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:52,391
<i>September 16th.</i>

249
00:14:53,492 --> 00:14:54,526
<i>Hospitalized again.</i>

250
00:14:56,295 --> 00:14:57,830
<i>Time is running out.</i>

251
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,766
<i>I called Akizumi.</i>

252
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:06,005
This…

253
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,340
is for you, Akizumi.

254
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:17,049
ITOI FAMILY MURDERS CASE

255
00:15:19,818 --> 00:15:21,587
You were still investigating it?

256
00:15:22,488 --> 00:15:23,322
Yeah.

257
00:15:26,859 --> 00:15:28,394
You're already busy,

258
00:15:29,461 --> 00:15:31,430
yet you traveled
between Tochigi and Chiba.

259
00:15:33,165 --> 00:15:35,000
And you neglected your regular checkups.

260
00:15:37,336 --> 00:15:39,338
You want to say I was foolish, right?

261
00:15:41,106 --> 00:15:42,374
Well, you're right.

262
00:15:44,810 --> 00:15:46,645
Now, look what's happened to me.

263
00:15:53,919 --> 00:15:56,255
Mr. Shimizu was definitely
falsely accused.

264
00:15:58,757 --> 00:16:00,559
If you read the file, you'll see.

265
00:16:02,661 --> 00:16:04,163
Akizumi…

266
00:16:06,365 --> 00:16:09,635
You bear responsibility
for coercing Mr. Shimizu into confessing.

267
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:14,039
Just once…

268
00:16:16,241 --> 00:16:17,810
please review the file.

269
00:16:55,814 --> 00:16:57,716
<i>To Akizumi.</i>

270
00:17:09,995 --> 00:17:11,964
<i>Save Mr. Shimizu.</i>

271
00:17:14,299 --> 00:17:16,301
<i>Now that I'm in this condition,
I understand.</i>

272
00:17:17,836 --> 00:17:19,905
<i>Life is limited</i>

273
00:17:20,506 --> 00:17:21,740
<i>and precious.</i>

274
00:17:23,142 --> 00:17:24,209
<i>I wish…</i>

275
00:17:26,779 --> 00:17:28,514
<i>I could have lived longer.</i>

276
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:32,985
<i>But…</i>

277
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:36,588
<i>there's a life that can still be saved.</i>

278
00:17:38,490 --> 00:17:39,758
<i>I wish that no one's life</i>

279
00:17:40,759 --> 00:17:44,963
<i>is taken away due to false accusations.</i>

280
00:17:46,365 --> 00:17:48,500
<i>Their lives should never be taken</i>

281
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:52,971
<i>because of the arrogance
of the justice authorities.</i>

282
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:55,808
<i>I strongly believe this…</i>

283
00:17:57,209 --> 00:17:59,645
<i>as one prosecutor.</i>

284
00:18:00,879 --> 00:18:01,914
<i>It is…</i>

285
00:18:03,015 --> 00:18:04,316
<i>my sincere hope…</i>

286
00:18:05,517 --> 00:18:11,190
<i>that we can restore trust and pride
in the justice system.</i>

287
00:18:33,645 --> 00:18:35,247
<i>I wanted to see this future</i>

288
00:18:36,515 --> 00:18:40,052
<i>with my own eyes too.</i>

289
00:18:43,822 --> 00:18:45,891
<i>Alongside Akizumi.</i>

290
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:04,042
Me too…

291
00:19:09,515 --> 00:19:10,582
Momose.

292
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:19,858
Here.

293
00:19:19,925 --> 00:19:21,493
It's from Ms. Momose's mother.

294
00:19:32,704 --> 00:19:33,906
I've gone through it all,

295
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:37,409
but I didn't find any clues
beyond what was already in the file.

296
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:38,477
I see.

297
00:19:43,115 --> 00:19:46,685
I'm sure Momose
must be grateful for your efforts.

298
00:19:47,486 --> 00:19:48,320
