00:31:55,079 --> 00:31:59,751
symptoms of vomiting, diarrhea,
ptosis, and flaccid paralysis."

510
00:31:59,817 --> 00:32:05,390
However, thallium does not cause symptoms
such as ptosis and flaccid paralysis.

511
00:32:06,291 --> 00:32:08,126
By the time of the interrogation,

512
00:32:08,192 --> 00:32:11,562
the results indicating thallium poisoning
should have been available.

513
00:32:11,629 --> 00:32:13,865
So, why did the detective
mention these symptoms?

514
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:16,935
It's possible it was just a mistake.

515
00:32:17,702 --> 00:32:20,738
But terms like
ptosis and flaccid paralysis

516
00:32:20,805 --> 00:32:24,809
are not commonly used unless referenced
from specific documents.

517
00:32:25,576 --> 00:32:27,879
What if this wasn't merely a mistake?

518
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:31,582
Perhaps someone intentionally altered
the poison test results.

519
00:32:32,250 --> 00:32:33,117
Yes.

520
00:32:33,184 --> 00:32:35,954
Testing poisons is complex
and identifying them takes time.

521
00:32:36,521 --> 00:32:39,524
Thallium sulfate,
easily accessible to Mr. Shimizu,

522
00:32:39,590 --> 00:32:41,960
would've been
compelling material for his indictment.

523
00:32:42,860 --> 00:32:45,630
Mr. Akizumi, you were called in
from the Saitama office

524
00:32:45,697 --> 00:32:47,999
during the final period
of Mr. Shimizu's detention.

525
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:50,234
By then, the results
had already been altered,

526
00:32:50,301 --> 00:32:52,170
leaving you no room for doubt.

527
00:32:53,438 --> 00:32:55,239
This is just the story we--

528
00:32:55,306 --> 00:32:58,109
If I were to add to your story,
it would go like this.

529
00:32:59,644 --> 00:33:01,446
Datehara was feeling frustrated.

530
00:33:02,113 --> 00:33:04,148
Despite having Mr. Shimizu in detention,

531
00:33:04,215 --> 00:33:06,451
<i>there wasn't
enough evidence to indict him.</i>

532
00:33:06,517 --> 00:33:07,986
<i>…such a cruel sight?!</i>

533
00:33:08,052 --> 00:33:12,390
At this rate, he risked losing Shimizu
due to insufficient evidence.

534
00:33:12,457 --> 00:33:13,491
<i>Let me see Saya!</i>

535
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:15,460
<i>This would set him back in uncovering </i>

536
00:33:15,526 --> 00:33:18,596
<i>the truth about the Nishi Chiba
Construction embezzlement too.</i>

537
00:33:18,663 --> 00:33:21,532
<i>For Datehara, this outcome
was absolutely unacceptable.</i>

538
00:33:22,166 --> 00:33:26,704
<i>"In that case, I'll fabricate evidence
that incriminates Shimizu," he thought.</i>

539
00:33:27,271 --> 00:33:28,940
With this in mind,

540
00:33:29,007 --> 00:33:33,411
<i>he instructed the head of the crime lab
to alter the test results</i>

541
00:33:34,212 --> 00:33:38,416
to indicate a poison that would cause
symptoms similar to the one used.

542
00:33:41,119 --> 00:33:42,020
Similar?

543
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:45,790
I see.

544
00:33:48,726 --> 00:33:49,961
SIMILAR?

545
00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:53,998
Momose had realized.

546
00:33:54,065 --> 00:33:55,333
I see.

547
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:57,869
By "similar," she meant the poison?

548
00:33:57,935 --> 00:34:00,505
There were a few books on poison, right?

549
00:34:00,571 --> 00:34:02,440
-Yes.
-Let's pull them all out.

550
00:34:02,507 --> 00:34:05,943
Let's list everything that shows
symptoms of ptosis and flaccid paralysis,

551
00:34:06,010 --> 00:34:07,512
and find one similar to thallium.

552
00:34:09,981 --> 00:34:11,115
Poliovirus.

553
00:34:12,283 --> 00:34:14,719
The timing for the onset
of symptoms doesn't match.

554
00:34:15,453 --> 00:34:16,654
Enterovirus.

555
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:18,623
This also doesn't fit the situation.

556
00:34:20,124 --> 00:34:22,326
Next is botulinum toxin.

557
00:34:22,894 --> 00:34:24,195
Botulinum toxin.

558
00:34:24,262 --> 00:34:27,432
Early symptoms include vomiting,
diarrhea, and other digestive issues.

559
00:34:27,498 --> 00:34:31,202
Later symptoms include ptosis,
blurred vision, difficulty swallowing…

560
00:34:32,103 --> 00:34:33,671
and flaccid paralysis.

561
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:35,039
It's similar.

562
00:34:35,606 --> 00:34:36,808
This must be it, right?

563
00:34:43,314 --> 00:34:44,515
This is it.

564
00:34:44,582 --> 00:34:46,217
So Momose had realized.

565
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:52,623
"Doctor."

566
00:34:52,690 --> 00:34:53,858
"Tampered"?

567
00:34:54,425 --> 00:34:55,293
"Tampered"?

568
00:34:55,359 --> 00:34:56,327
Perhaps this means…

569
00:34:56,961 --> 00:34:59,831
Momose realized something
after consulting with a doctor.

570
00:34:59,897 --> 00:35:02,900
I've heard from Ms. Momose's mother
that even while hospitalized,

571
00:35:02,967 --> 00:35:06,571
Momose kept investigating the case
and consulted doctors about poisons.

572
00:35:06,637 --> 00:35:10,141
She discovered the possible tampering
and intended to investigate it further.

573
00:35:10,842 --> 00:35:13,277
Mr. Aoyama, do you know
who conducted the poison test?

574
00:35:13,344 --> 00:35:16,080
Satoshi Hiratsuka.
He resigned and now lives in Nerima Ward.

575
00:35:16,147 --> 00:35:17,548
I'll go talk to him right away.

576
00:35:17,615 --> 00:35:18,749
Do so.

577
00:35:19,417 --> 00:35:20,284
Also…

578
00:35:21,519 --> 00:35:22,687
Ms. Shinomiya…

579
00:35:28,993 --> 00:35:31,195
You've finally agreed to see us.

580
00:35:31,963 --> 00:35:34,165
I've come to say something to you.

581
00:35:34,832 --> 00:35:36,200
Stop involving my daughter!

582
00:35:36,267 --> 00:35:37,135
Dad!

583
00:35:37,201 --> 00:35:40,404
Unfortunately,
I have no intention of letting her go.

584
00:35:41,372 --> 00:35:43,307
Your daughter is still valuable to me.

585
00:35:43,374 --> 00:35:44,275
How dare you!

586
00:35:44,342 --> 00:35:45,776
What do you take my daughter for?!

587
00:35:45,843 --> 00:35:49,046
She's an exceptionally skilled
and useful subordinate.

588
00:35:49,614 --> 00:35:52,016
She's particularly effective
at shaking you up.

589
00:35:53,918 --> 00:35:56,621
I'm here today
because I need to ask you something.

590
00:35:58,589 --> 00:36:00,925
It's about the Itoi family murders.

591
00:36:04,095 --> 00:36:05,429
I won't tell you anything.

592
00:36:05,496 --> 00:36:06,998
Is that for your daughter?

593
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:11,502
Datehara is quite ruthless, isn't he?

594
00:36:12,069 --> 00:36:14,305
He's taken your daughter as hostage.

595
00:36:15,873 --> 00:36:19,477
If you're not careful with your words,
your daughter's future could be ruined.

596
00:36:19,544 --> 00:36:21,379
You may not care if you're arrested,

597
00:36:22,113 --> 00:36:23,848
but you'll protect your daughter.

598
00:36:24,682 --> 00:36:27,785
What a beautiful display of paternal love.

599
00:36:29,787 --> 00:36:31,122
What does that mean?

600
00:36:34,759 --> 00:36:37,361
So you've kept silent all this time…

601
00:36:40,665 --> 00:36:42,033
for my sake?

602
00:36:46,070 --> 00:36:47,238
Just go already.

603
00:36:47,939 --> 00:36:49,040
Give me a break!

604
00:36:51,309 --> 00:36:52,743
So what about my future?

605
00:36:53,978 --> 00:36:56,914
I couldn't care less about it!

606
00:36:58,049 --> 00:37:02,186
Mr. Shimizu was falsely accused
and has no idea when he'll be executed!

607
00:37:04,956 --> 00:37:09,126
What future could possibly outweigh
someone's life?

608
00:37:12,830 --> 00:37:14,398
And you realize, don't you?

609
00:37:15,433 --> 00:37:19,403
That if Mr. Shimizu didn't do it,
the real culprit is still out there!

610
00:37:20,838 --> 00:37:22,006
And yet…

611
00:37:22,974 --> 00:37:25,042
you've turned a blind eye for years.

612
00:37:25,109 --> 00:37:26,177
How can you…

613
00:37:28,346 --> 00:37:30,281
call yourself a police officer?

614
00:37:36,053 --> 00:37:37,255
In Mr. Shimizu's notebook…

615
00:37:39,023 --> 00:37:41,993
the latter half is all about Saya.

616
00:37:42,493 --> 00:37:44,929
"I want to see her."

617
00:37:44,996 --> 00:37:46,030
I WANT TO SEE HER

618
00:37:46,097 --> 00:37:47,999
Can you even imagine…

619
00:37:48,065 --> 00:37:49,400
I WANT TO SEE SAYA BEFORE I DIE

620
00:37:50,134 --> 00:37:52,303
…how Mr. Shimizu must have felt?

621
00:37:55,506 --> 00:37:56,340
Come on.

622
00:37:57,041 --> 00:37:58,676
Answer me, Dad!

623
00:38:10,755 --> 00:38:12,623
I have imagined it.

624
00:38:13,658 --> 00:38:14,625
Countless times.

625
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:18,229
Over and over!

626
00:38:21,132 --> 00:38:22,800
When I saw that footage,

627
00:38:22,867 --> 00:38:26,170
honestly, I thought
I should make it public immediately.

628
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:28,172
But…

629
00:38:29,674 --> 00:38:30,608
<i>By then…</i>

630
00:38:31,309 --> 00:38:33,611
<i>Shimizu's trial had already started.</i>

631
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:38,783
I'll only say this once.

632
00:38:40,751 --> 00:38:42,086
The police…

633
00:38:42,853 --> 00:38:46,090
never found this footage.

634
00:38:48,059 --> 00:38:49,660
-But…
-No buts!

635
00:38:51,962 --> 00:38:54,065
You're telling me now that he's innocent?

636
00:38:54,632 --> 00:38:55,666
Get real!

637
00:38:57,535 --> 00:38:59,203
Imagine making this public!

638
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:02,973
This won't just be
your responsibility or mine!

639
00:39:04,442 --> 00:39:09,480
Resigning and abandoning our duties
is out of the question!

640
00:39:09,547 --> 00:39:11,549
That won't absolve us in any way!

641
00:39:12,450 --> 00:39:14,485
Shimizu's family has been torn apart,

642
00:39:14,552 --> 00:39:15,920
and his wife has passed away.

643
00:39:17,088 --> 00:39:21,559
The media will accuse us
of causing her death,

644
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:25,896
saying, "They deserve the same fate."
"Murderers."

645
00:39:25,963 --> 00:39:31,402
The public's harsh scrutiny
will mercilessly fall on our families!

646
00:39:31,469 --> 00:39:32,770
Even on your daughter!

647
00:39:36,173 --> 00:39:37,241
This…

648
00:39:39,043 --> 00:39:40,378
isn't a threat.

649
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:44,749
I'm going to have a child soon…

650
00:39:46,817 --> 00:39:50,454
after waiting for so long!

651
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:57,361
I will bear…

652
00:39:59,663 --> 00:40:01,565
the same cross as you.

653
00:40:09,373 --> 00:40:10,441
<i>I feel…</i>

654
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:13,878
very sorry…

655
00:40:15,446 --> 00:40:17,114
for Mr. Shimizu.

656
00:40:18,916 --> 00:40:19,850
But now…

657
00:40:21,152 --> 00:40:22,052
it can't…

658
00:40:23,554 --> 00:40:24,822
be undone.

659
00:40:24,889 --> 00:40:25,756
"You murderer!"

660
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,629
To escape that accusation…

661
00:40:32,596 --> 00:40:35,232
you're going to let a person die,
is that it?

662
00:40:37,368 --> 00:40:38,803
As you've said,

663
00:40:38,869 --> 00:40:42,973
even if you regret it now,
the past can never be undone.

664
00:40:45,776 --> 00:40:47,411
But the future is different.

665
00:40:48,913 --> 00:40:52,716
You can still save Mr. Shimizu's life.

666
00:40:56,487 --> 00:40:58,489
Tell me, Mr. Kurata.

667
00:41:00,491 --> 00:41:03,727
The poison used
in the Itoi family murders,

668
00:41:03,794 --> 00:41:06,597
it wasn't really thallium sulfate, was it?

669
00:41:09,200 --> 00:41:12,369
The poison test results were altered!

670
00:41:15,339 --> 00:41:16,273
Dad…

671
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:20,644
It's possible.

672
00:41:21,712 --> 00:41:23,347
Early in the investigation,

673
00:41:24,315 --> 00:41:26,383
there was confusion regarding the poison.

674
00:41:27,618 --> 00:41:31,288
<i>But then, someone
from the crime lab came with a report.</i>

675
00:41:31,856 --> 00:41:35,726
<i>He said that thallium sulfate
was detected on the table,</i>

676
00:41:35,793 --> 00:41:38,529
<i>and the same substance
was found on the bodies.</i>

677
00:41:39,430 --> 00:41:41,999
I understand
identifying poisons is tricky.

678
00:41:43,434 --> 00:41:46,003
It often requires a great amount of time.

679
00:41:48,138 --> 00:41:48,973
So…

680
00:41:50,074 --> 00:41:52,142
I didn't think
it was particularly unusual.

681
00:41:53,143 --> 00:41:55,513
Can you confirm
that the person from the crime lab…

682
00:41:56,714 --> 00:41:58,782
was Satoshi Hiratsuka?

683
00:42:00,084 --> 00:42:01,018
I can.

684
00:42:02,987 --> 00:42:03,854
But…

685
00:42:11,362 --> 00:42:12,496
<i>I see.</i>

686
00:42:12,563 --> 00:42:13,430
<i>Yes.</i>

687
00:42:13,497 --> 00:42:16,100
He passed away
three years ago due to illness.

688
00:42:17,334 --> 00:42:19,670
Find Hiratsuka's former assistant.

689
00:42:20,905 --> 00:42:21,805
<i>Right.</i>

690
00:42:33,984 --> 00:42:36,654
I've made a list of people
who were Hiratsuka's assistants.

691
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:38,956
I think I can meet
with some of them this week.

692
00:42:39,757 --> 00:42:40,591
Akamine…

693
00:42:41,759 --> 00:42:43,160
thank you for your help.

694
00:42:44,662 --> 00:42:47,197
I hope we can uncover even a small clue.

695
00:42:56,974 --> 00:42:57,841
Hey!

696
00:42:58,842 --> 00:42:59,677
What's this about?

697
00:42:59,743 --> 00:43:00,611
We're the police.

698
00:43:00,678 --> 00:43:02,413
Is Mr. Masaki Akizumi here?

699
00:43:02,479 --> 00:43:03,547
Why do you want him?

700
00:43:05,449 --> 00:43:06,850
-Hey.
-Hey, hold on!

701
00:43:06,917 --> 00:43:07,952
-Hey!
-You can't!

702
00:43:08,018 --> 00:43:09,219
-Wait!
-Hey!

703
00:43:09,787 --> 00:43:10,721
It's the police.

704
00:43:11,655 --> 00:43:13,190
Are you Mr. Masaki Akizumi?

705
00:43:14,992 --> 00:43:17,094
We have an arrest warrant for you

706
00:43:17,161 --> 00:43:20,264
for covering up evidence in the murder
of Hanegi Seiko's president.

707
00:43:20,831 --> 00:43:21,932
Come on, stand up.

708
00:43:22,700 --> 00:43:23,901
Arrest?

709
00:43:24,702 --> 00:43:25,703
Let's go.

710
00:43:28,839 --> 00:43:30,074
Begin searching.

711
00:43:30,140 --> 00:43:31,308
-Right.
-Right.

712
00:43:40,351 --> 00:43:41,685
-Come in.
-Excuse me.

713
00:43:42,586 --> 00:43:45,889
It appears Akizumi was arrested earlier.

714
00:43:46,490 --> 00:43:48,258
Was he now?

715
00:43:48,325 --> 00:43:50,794
Poor guy.

716
00:43:50,861 --> 00:43:51,862
Do you think so?

717
00:43:55,065 --> 00:43:57,334
I think it's only what he deserves.

718
00:43:58,969 --> 00:44:02,172
But are you sure?

719
00:44:02,806 --> 00:44:06,410
You were somewhat in his debt,
weren't you?

720
00:44:08,012 --> 00:44:10,314
HIYAMA

721
00:44:10,381 --> 00:44:11,715
Not really.

722
00:44:12,282 --> 00:44:15,653
After a skilled attorney joined,
he didn't need me anymore.

723
00:44:19,723 --> 00:44:23,327
Should I work on Akizumi's trial?

724
00:44:24,128 --> 00:44:25,129
No.

725
00:44:25,963 --> 00:44:27,431
I'll handle it.

726
00:44:30,601 --> 00:44:32,836
For Akizumi's sake as well,

727
00:44:32,903 --> 00:44:36,473
let's put an end to this.

728
00:44:54,725 --> 00:44:55,626
Mr. Akizumi!

729
00:44:59,763 --> 00:45:01,065
I'll leave the rest to you.

730
00:45:20,317 --> 00:45:22,319
Subtitle translation by: Ai Matsuoka

731
00:45:23,287 --> 00:45:27,224
I've dreamed of seeing you
like this for a long time.

732
00:45:27,291 --> 00:45:29,293
How could he conceal evidence of murder?

733
00:45:29,359 --> 00:45:30,194
I killed him.

734
00:45:30,260 --> 00:45:31,695
He must have left something.

735
00:45:31,762 --> 00:45:32,896
I have something to say.

736
00:45:32,963 --> 00:45:34,331
A precious life is at stake.

737
00:45:34,398 --> 00:45:35,399
I couldn't believe her.

738
00:45:35,466 --> 00:45:37,468
-Shimizu is a criminal!
-Objection!

739
00:45:37,534 --> 00:45:38,969
There's something only I can do.

740
00:45:39,036 --> 00:45:40,237
We will bear the responsibility.

741
00:45:40,304 --> 00:45:43,440
People compete and take from each other.
That's just how the world works.

742
00:45:43,507 --> 00:45:46,677
Together, let's go to hell.

